{
  "stem": "717.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And of course there were people that had hidden radios.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Two very close friends of mine had a radio and they carried it in two little parts, separated, and they listened to the radio and we had the news continuously.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If they'd been caught, they would kill them on the spot or send to Auschwitz right away.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was funny to see.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One was a very prominent Jewish leader of the community in Melbourne, Australia, and the other one lives in Australia.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Very [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were just here visiting us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[HEBREW] Vina was about 6'3', and [INAUDIBLE], my friend, was barely five feet.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was funny to see those two guys walk in the ghetto with these two parts.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he carried half the radio and he carried half the radio.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we had news all the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That's how we knew about Auschwitz, about the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They listened to London radio, you know, underground radios.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the final blow came [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in the middle of 1944, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when the-- the [NON-ENGLISH], the German [NON-ENGLISH] of the ghetto, Hans [INAUDIBLE], [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he couldn't hold onto it any longer.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He wanted to hold it because as long as he held onto the ghetto, not only did he make money-- he was like a Schindler, like Oskar, but in a different way.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Not-- he didn't risk his life, quite the opposite.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He worked for the Germans, very legally.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But it saved his life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They didn't send him to the Army.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
